snippet.title: Man dies in Central Coast crash
snippet.content:
A man has died after a car veered off the road and hit a tree on the Central Coast.
Emergency services were called to Wilfred Barrett Drive, Magenta, just after 11am on Saturday after reports a car had hit a tree.
NSW Paramedics treated a man, but he died at the scene.
Officers from Tuggerah Lakes Local Area Command established a crime scene and have started an investigation into circumstances surrounding the incident. A report will be prepared for the Coroner.
